        {
            "title": "Our resources",
            "blocks": [
                "Our greatest strength is in the people who are with us. In 2013, National Societies reported that they had a membership of 80 million. They had some 452,000 paid staff and mobilised a further 16 million volunteers, giving an overall volunteer to staff ratio of 35 to 1, with just under half of the volunteers being female",
                {
                    "type": "chart",
                    "title": "Human Resources in National Societies",
                    "translations": {
                        "volunteers": "Volunteers",
                        "paidStaff": "Paid staff",
                        "secretariatStaff": "Secretariat staff",
                        "male": "Male",
                        "female": "Female",
                        "nationalSocietyStaff": "National Society Staff",
                        "nationalSocietyVolunteers": "National Society Volunteers",
                        "IFRCSecretariatStaff": "IFRC Secretariat Staff"
                    },
                    "caption": "Source: FDRS, Human Resources Department"
                },
                "National Societies received an income of about 30.8 billion Swiss francs and spent 30.4 billion Swiss francs in 2013. Most of the income of National Societies is raised and spent domestically on their own programmes. This does not capture the total value of Red Cross and Red Crescent work, because it does not include the many in-kind domestic contributions and services provided voluntarily.",
                "National Societies gave 35.4 million Swiss francs in statutory membership fees to the IFRC secretariat. This, together with an additional 263 million Swiss francs in voluntary contributions, and services and other income of 47.1 million Swiss francs, made up the IFRC secretariat\u2019s income of 345.5 million Swiss francs in 2013. During the same year, the IFRC secretariat spent 365.3 million Swiss francs and employed 2,920 staff.",
                {
