                "Each National Society is unique and its profile can be consulted on www.ifrc.org\/data. At the same time, the IFRC is founded on the notion of mutually respectful solidarity among National Societies through sharing knowledge, practical expertise, other capacities, and financial resources.",
                "However, we do not know the total magnitude of what National Societies spend in international assistance, as much of this is done bilaterally. The Federation-wide Databank and Reporting System will seek to reflect this in the future. Meanwhile, an indication can be found in the response to IFRC appeals. Between 2010 and 2014, National Societies, governments, and others contributed more than 1.5 billion Swiss francs. There are considerable year-on-year fluctuations, mostly due to the pattern of major emergencies.",
